Patched entry
-------------
pyfreeimage/funct_list.pyc

Byte-preserving patch
---------------------
The marshalled string constant:

    FreeImage_RotateClassic

was replaced with the same-length string:

    FreeImage_MakeThumbnail

This avoids binding the missing RotateClassic export at startup. The resulting
function list has a duplicate MakeThumbnail entry and no RotateClassic entry.

Known caveat
------------
Quivi's image rotation action will still need a follow-up patch, because
pyfreeimage/image.pyc still calls self._lib.RotateClassic when rotation is used.
Static WebP opening is unaffected.

